Document: SubViewport
Path: godot/classes/class_subviewport.rst
Summary: A SubViewport node is a special kind of Viewport that can be rendered to a texture.

SubViewport

Inherits: Viewport < Node < Object

A SubViewport node is a special kind of Viewport that can be rendered to a texture. This allows you to create render targets for your scenes, which can then be used in other scenes, for example, as a texture on a Sprite or a MeshInstance.

SubViewportContainer

Inherits: Container < Control < CanvasItem < Node < Object

A container that makes its SubViewport child fit its size.

This node is useful for displaying a SubViewport within a UI. It automatically resizes the SubViewport to match the container's size, ensuring that the rendered output is always displayed correctly.
