Document: SubViewport
Path: godot/classes/class_subviewport.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the SubViewport class, including clear mode, update mode, size, and view count.

Properties:
* render_target_clear_mode (ClearMode): Determines how the render target is cleared each frame. Default: 0.
* render_target_update_mode (UpdateMode): Controls when the render target is updated. Default: 2.
* size (Vector2i): The size of the render target in pixels. Default: Vector2i(512, 512).
* size_2d_override (Vector2i): Overrides the 2D size of the viewport. Default: Vector2i(0, 0).
* size_2d_override_stretch (bool): If true, the 2D size override will be stretched to fit the viewport. Default: false.
* view_count (int): The number of views the SubViewport renders. Default: 1.
---CHUNK---
Document: SubViewport
Path: godot/classes/class_subviewport.rst
Summary: Defines enumeration constants for controlling how a SubViewport's render target is cleared and updated.

Enumerations:
ClearMode:
  CLEAR_MODE_ALWAYS = 0: Always clear the render target before drawing.
  CLEAR_MODE_NEVER = 1: Never clear the render target.
  CLEAR_MODE_ONCE = 2: Clear the render target on the next frame, then switch to CLEAR_MODE_NEVER.

UpdateMode:
  UPDATE_DISABLED = 0: Do not update the render target.
  UPDATE_ONCE = 1: Update the render target once, then switch to UPDATE_DISABLED.
  UPDATE_WHEN_VISIBLE = 2: Update the render target only when it is visible. This is the default value.
  UPDATE_WHEN_PARENT_VISIBLE = 3: Update the render target only when its parent is visible.
  UPDATE_ALWAYS = 4: Always update the render target.
---CHUNK---
Document: SubViewport
Path: godot/classes/class_subviewport.rst
Summary: Properties for configuring the rendering behavior and size of a SubViewport.

Property: render_target_clear_mode
Type: ClearMode
Default: 0
Description: The clear mode when the sub-viewport is used as a render target. Note: This property is intended for 2D usage.
Setters: set_clear_mode(value: ClearMode)
Getters: get_clear_mode() → ClearMode

Property: render_target_update_mode
Type: UpdateMode
Default: 2
Description: The update mode when the sub-viewport is used as a render target.
Setters: set_update_mode(value: UpdateMode)
Getters: get_update_mode() → UpdateMode

Property: size
Type: Vector2i
Default: Vector2i(512, 512)
Description: The width and height of the sub-viewport. Must be set to a value greater than or equal to 2 pixels on both dimensions. Otherwise, nothing will be displayed. Note: If the parent node is a SubViewportContainer and its SubViewportContainer.stretch is true, the viewport size cannot be changed manually.
Setters: set_size(value: Vector2i)
Getters: get_size() → Vector2i

Property: size_2d_override
Type: Vector2i
Default: Vector2i(0, 0)
Description: The 2D size override of the sub-viewport. If either the width or height is 0, the override is disabled.
Setters: set_size_2d_override(value: Vector2i)
Getters: get_size_2d_override() → Vector2i

Property: size_2d_override_stretch
Type: bool
Default: false
Description: If true, the 2D size override affects stretch as well.
Setters: set_size_2d_override_stretch(value: bool)
Getters: is_size_2d_override_stretch_enabled() → bool

Property: view_count
Type: int
Default: 1
Description: The number of view layers we are rendering to. Set this to 2 to enable stereo rendering.
Setters: set_view_count(value: int)
Getters: get_view_count() → int